h3. Problem Definition
There is currently no variable for pull request hashes.
h3. Suggested Solution
Add a Bamboo variable, such as $\{bamboo.repository.pullRequest}
h3. Workaround
As a workaround, you can use your version control system's API. Below are examples of possible GitHub and Bitbucket Server API calls.
h4. GitHub
{code:title=API call}curl -s -u<username>:<personal-access-token> https://api.github.com/repos/<owner>/<repository>/pulls | grep merge_commit_sha|awk -F'"' '{print $4}'{code}
h4. Bitbucket Server
{code:title=API call}curl -s -u<username>:<pasword> "<bitbucket-url>/rest/api/1.0/projects/<project-key>/repos/<repo-slug>/pull-requests"|json_pp|grep 'latestCommit\|Ref'
Enter host password for user 'ezeidan':
         "toRef" : {
            "latestCommit" : "9f99052b726d18a3c8d62ba9e02f0d09519bedfa",
         "fromRef" : {
            "latestCommit" : "92006c7ce897a0fb4d8faacd7a0d79d887728925",
{code}

h2. HTR
Consider the following code:
{code}
        final BitbucketCloudRepository bitbucketRepository = new BitbucketCloudRepository()
                .name("repo")
                .repositorySlug("owner", "repository")
                .branch("master");

        final GitRepository gitRepository = new GitRepository()
                .name("repo")
                .url("file:///tmp/repository");
        
        bambooServer.publish(gitRepository);
        bambooServer.publish(bitbucketRepository);
{code}

h2. Expected behaviour

Bamboo gives meaningful error message about linked repository name uniqueness and the name clash.

h2. Actual behaviour

Bamboo gives cryptic error message:
{noformat}
Exception in thread "main" com.atlassian.bamboo.specs.api.exceptions.BambooSpecsPublishingException: An error occurred while publishing repository repo: Repository type can not be changed. Was: com.atlassian.bamboo.plugins.atlassian-bamboo-plugin-git:gitv2, new: com.atlassian.bamboo.plugins.atlassian-bamboo-plugin-bitbucket:bbCloud
{noformat}
